OL,3,CGovernment announces inquiry into
OL,4,CBattle of Orgreave
OL,6,FMs Flannery added: "We now need to be
OL,7,Fsatisfied that the inquiry is given
OL,8,Fthe necessary powers to fully
OL,9,Finvestigate all the aspects of the
OL,10,Forchestrated policing at Orgreave, and
OL,11,Fhave unrestricted access to all
OL,12,Frelevant information including
OL,13,Fgovernment, police and media
OL,14,Fdocuments, photos and films."
OL,16,FThe National Union of Mineworkers
OL,17,F(NUM) general secretary, Chris
OL,18,FKitchen, said the inquiry was "hugely
OL,19,Fwelcome".
OL,26,@nD@TOUvD@]O]zD@_OU{D@HO]
